This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it presents a new method that combines active and semi-supervised deep learning to achieve high generalization performance from a deep convolutional neural network with as few known labels as possible. The paper also uses the MNIST dataset, which is commonly used in machine learning research. 

It is also likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the paper uses a deep convolutional neural network, which is a common architecture used in computer vision tasks. 

The paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it presents a new method for improving the accuracy of deep learning models, which is a common area of research in AI. 

It may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper discusses the process of generating label information, which is a common task in natural language processing. 

Finally, it may belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper uses a deep neural network, which is a common tool in neural computing research.
